{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"ea58b3ee-2635-43c6-9208-2686303eba47","content":"Use `Assert.ThrowsException` (MSTest) or `Assert.Throws` (xUnit/NUnit) instead:\n\n```csharp\n[TestMethod]\npublic void CreateUser_NullEmail_ThrowsException()\n{\n    var service = new UserService();\n\n    var ex = Assert.ThrowsException<ArgumentNullException>(\n        () => service.CreateUser(null, \"John\"));\n\n    Assert.AreEqual(\"email\", ex.ParamName); // bonus: assert on details\n}\n```\n\n**Why migrate:**\n- `[ExpectedException]` can't verify *which line* threw — if the constructor throws instead, the test still passes incorrectly.\n- `Assert.ThrowsException` scopes the assertion to the exact call and returns the exception so you can inspect its properties.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"9e31f4cb-b514-436e-b106-84adec4fa72c","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about modernizing a C# test that uses the `[ExpectedException]` attribute. This is a straightforward knowledge question — no tools needed.","outputTokens":242,"requestId":"042A:1EAE:274326:37051F:69E82130"},"id":"d774e9d0-8a85-431d-a8dd-98c829a5bdc1","timestamp":"2026-04-22T01:15:33.789Z","parentId":"5122abf9-18fd-47d5-aef0-03802b136bfd"}
